text: O'Toole is an Irish surname. It may refer to: == People == *O'Toole (family) *O'Toole (surname) ===Other uses=== * Erin O'Toole, (b. 1973) leader of the Opposition of Canada and leader of the Conservative Party of Canada since August 24, 2020 * Peter O'Toole (1932-2013), British actor * Annette O'Toole (b. 1952) American actress, dancer, and singer-songwriter * O'Tooles GAC football and hurling club in Dublin * Ensign O'Toole, a military sitcom starring Dean Jones, which aired on NBC, 1962-1963 * Ensign O'Toole and Me, the title of a semi-autobiographical novel by William Lederer * Plenty O'Toole, James Bond girl * Slugger O'Toole, Irish weblog * St. Laurence O'Toole Pipe Band * Sneakers O'Toole Family Guy Character (Boys Do Cry) * Timmy O'Toole Bart's fictional character who fell down a well in an episode of the Simpsons * , the name of more than one United States Navy ship ==See also== *Other anglicizations of ó Tuathail: ** Tohill ** Toal (disambiguation)
title: O'Toole
